我正在回复一个期刊审稿意见，请你根据审稿人的意见为我提出一些合适的回复角度：\item {\sf ``\textbf{Dependency on the Underlying GAN (GET3D):}
The method fully relies on GET3D as the 3D generator, but all experiments focus on rigid object categories like cars and chairs. Although GET3D supports more complex categories (e.g., animals, humans, buildings), these are not evaluated, raising concerns about generalization.
Suggestion for Revision:
Include examples from diverse categories supported by GET3D and clarify whether observed limitations arise from the generator or from ToW3D++ itself.''}
